The evidence with the title 'Standard & Poor's downgrades us credit rating from aaa to aa+ ... ' says Aug 5, 2011  ... Last month , Standard & Poor's warned that the U.S. risked a downgrade to aa status if Congress did not lift the debt ceiling and reduce the total debt by $ 4 trillion over the next decade . The eventual deal called for barely half as much deficit reduction . S&P: 'we could lower the long-term rating to aa'. 
